<td valign="top">
<p><img height="225" width="300" src="http://www.edenhrconsulting.com/images/stories/eden-stick-figures/eden-rules-regulations.jpg" alt="eden-rules-regulations" style="float: right;" />We sincerely hope that you realise just how important contracts of employment are; firstly, you have a legal obligation to provide a written statement of terms and conditions of employment within two months of commencement of employment. If you don’t, and the relationship ends up in an employment tribunal, then you may receive an additional fine for non-issue of contract.</p>
<p>Apart from the fact that there is a legal obligation to provide contracts, they can also help to protect your business. They provide a clear and unequivocal statement of terms and conditions between you and your employees. By providing correct terms and conditions of employment, you are not only protecting your business from potential claims, but also setting the standard of communication between both parties and setting behavioural expectations of your employees.</p></td>
</tr>

